sentence.text: Furthermore, a series of experiments and rescue experiments revealed that Nuclear Receptor Subfamily 3 Group C Member 2 (NR3C2) was the target of miR-135b-5p in pancreatic cancer cells, mediating the promotion effects of miR-135b-5p on the tumor cells migration, invasion and cytokine production.
Additionally, immunohistochemistry staining and Western blot showed that highly expressed miR-135b-5p accelerated cytokine production process of pancreatic cancer cells.

This study aimed to elucidate the potential functional mechanism of protein polyubiquitination-135b-5p in migration, invasion and epithelial-to-mesenchymal transition (EMT) of pancreatic cancer cells.
